fullDescription.text:
Reports cases when any call to 'super(A, B)' does not meet the following requirements: 'B' is an instance of 'A' 'B' a subclass of 'A' Example: 'class Figure:
    def color(self):
        pass


class Rectangle(Figure):
    def color(self):
        pass


class Square(Figure):
    def color(self):
        return super(Rectangle, self).color() # Square is not an instance or subclass of Rectangle' As a fix, you can make the 'Square' an instance of the 'Rectangle' class. Inspection ID: PySuperArgumentsInspection

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports cases when any call to `super(A, B)` does not meet the
following requirements:

* `B` is an instance of `A`
* `B` a subclass of `A`

**Example:**


    class Figure:
        def color(self):
            pass


    class Rectangle(Figure):
        def color(self):
            pass


    class Square(Figure):
        def color(self):
            return super(Rectangle, self).color() # Square is not an instance or subclass of Rectangle

As a fix, you can make the `Square` an instance of the `Rectangle` class.

Inspection ID: PySuperArgumentsInspection

